<font color="#FF0000">U.S.M.C.  HONORED BY INDIANS</font><br>
<tt>Wed Aug 20  0:10:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
COOK BARELA LEADS U.S.M.C. To High level of Recognition<br><br>
Comanche Reservation, Aug. 19, Tatekohomni Wambli Reporting.<br><br>
    A gathering of fierce Comanche and Lakota holy men and Medicine men recently invited Madman M-60 Machine Gunner, Jarhead, Flat foot, Cook Barela to a Dog Roast.<br>
    Mr. Barela, was unaware that Native Americans honor their brothers who behave very strangely (walk backwards... ride horses backwards... cry at funny jokes... laugh at tragic events... etc.)<br>
     When the Elk Skin Award was unrolled and translated into English in a very solemn ceremony... that is until Mr. Barela began screaming at his hosts in a most violent manner...When he learned that U.S.M.C stood for unstable, severe, mental case.<br>
     Cook was heard screaming, &quot;The only good Indian is a dead Indian,&quot; as he stomped out of the village.<br>
     The elders smiled and nodded their heads in approval.  In unison, they uttered, &quot;Good....Choice!&quot;<br><br>
Humming Eagle Reporting from on the scene.<br><br>
P.S.  Second runner-up Doctor Barry Spatz (even though he has been the recipient of this award for the last twenty consecutive years)will fill the vacated position.  A special council was called to review the qualifications of a mystery man know only as &quot;Silent Warrior.&quot;<br><br>

